---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<section
  id="about"
  class="about-paper-texture text-copy-ink"
  aria-labelledby="about-title"
  tabindex="-1"
>
  <header
    class="content-shell grid place-items-center py-16 lg:py-24"
  >
    <p
      class="max-w-5xl text-center font-heading text-2xl leading-snug text-balance text-ink uppercase sm:text-3xl lg:text-5xl"
      data-about-intro
    >
      Independent print photography zine and archive, published every two months
      and built through open calls for photographs taken across Europe
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="content-shell section-title-container">
    <h2
      id="about-title"
      class="section-title-tile section-title-tile-about mx-auto -rotate-1 shadow-xl"
      data-stamp-title
    >
      <span class="sr-only">About</span>
      <img
        class="section-title-art title-palette-blue"
        src={`${base}/images/section_names_img/about-cropped.webp`}
        srcset={`${base}/images/section_names_img/about-cropped-256.webp 256w, ${base}/images/section_names_img/about-cropped.webp 448w`}
        sizes="(min-width: 80rem) 18.7rem, (min-width: 40rem) 25vw, 33vw"
        alt=""
        width="448"
        height="180"
        loading="lazy"
        aria-hidden="true"
      />
    </h2>
  </div>

  <div
    class="content-shell py-16 lg:py-28"
  >
    <div
      class="grid gap-6 font-body text-base leading-relaxed [text-wrap:wrap] sm:text-lg sm:text-pretty lg:gap-10 lg:text-2xl"
    >
      <p>
        Founded, edited, and designed by photographer and designer Petra Zegnal,
        {' '}
        <strong class="font-bold">SALTPRINT</strong> is an independent one-woman
        project born from a love of photography, graphic design, print, and a
        desire to give something back to the photography community. It was created
        to give photographs more time, space, and permanence than they often
        receive online. Instead of disappearing into an endless feed, each selected
        photograph becomes part of a printed archive.
      </p>

      <p>
        Every archive starts somewhere. Ours begins in{' '}
        <strong class="font-bold">Europe;</strong>{' '}its landscapes, cities, and
        everyday life. As SALTPRINT grows, future volumes may look beyond Europe.
      </p>

      <p>
        You do not need to live in Europe to submit. You do not need a large
        following, a professional portfolio, or an expensive camera. All you need
        is one photograph taken in Europe and a few words about why it mattered to
        you.
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong class="font-bold"
          >SALTPRINT welcomes photographers at every stage of their journey.</strong
        >{' '}Whether you're just beginning, studying photography, teaching
        yourself, or sharing your work for the first time, your photographs are
        welcome here.
      </p>

      <p>
        Each volume brings together a selection of photographs from the open call.
        Three selected photographers are also invited to take part in a short
        interview, sharing more about themselves and the story behind their
        photograph.
      </p>

      <p class="font-bold">
        SALTPRINT is published every two months. One growing archive. Built
        together.
      </p>

      <p class="pt-6 font-bold text-ink lg:pt-8">
        Feel free to follow us on{' '}
        <a
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-[#2c435b] underline decoration-1 underline-offset-4 transition-opacity hover:opacity-75 focus-visible:rounded-sm focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-4 focus-visible:outline-[#2c435b] motion-reduce:transition-none"
          href="https://www.instagram.com/saltprint_zine/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer"
          aria-label="Follow Saltprint on Instagram"
        >
          <span>INSTAGRAM</span>
          <svg
            class="size-[1em] shrink-0"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            fill="none"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
            stroke-linecap="round"
            stroke-linejoin="round"
            aria-hidden="true"
          >
            <rect x="2" y="2" width="20" height="20" rx="5"></rect>
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="4"></circle>
            <circle cx="17.5" cy="6.5" r="1" fill="currentColor" stroke="none"></circle>
          </svg>
        </a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<script src="../../scripts/motion/aboutIntro.ts"></script>
